If @code{f} is a function of 2 or more arguments, outativity is defined as in
the case of @code{sum} or @code{integrate}, i.e., @code{f (a*g(x), x)} will
simplify to @code{a * f(g(x), x)} for @code{a} free of @code{x}.
@end enumerate

